Up for sale is my 9mm P226 Tacops. It has the standard Tacops TFO front site and SIGLITE rear sight with some life left in them. Also has the short reset trigger and magwell grip. I'm not sure of the round count as I am not the first owner of this handgun. I have personally put about 300-400 rounds down range, and it functions flawlessly. It will come with 2 factory 20 rnd magazines, 2 Mecgar 20 rd magazines, and a Blackhawk Serpa holster. The lower has been duracoated in flat dark earth and the slide duracoated in black. After about two years of shooting and handling, you can see that some of the paint has chipped off, however, it does not affect the function. This handgun is not a beauty/safe queen but is always ready for combat!
No bill of sale required, but I would like to see your GA driver's license and GA weapons carry license."

The powerful and versatile SureFire X300 Ultra WeaponLight features a high-performance LED that generates 500 lumens of stunning white light focused by a Total Internal Reflection (TIR) lens to produce a tight beam with extended reach and significant surround light for peripheral vision. The virtually indestructible and highly efficient LED generates tactical-level light more than enough to overwhelm an aggressor's dark-adapted vision for 1.5 hours per set of batteries. The high-strength aerospace aluminum body is Mil-Spec hard anodized for superior toughness and is O-ring and gasket sealed to make it weatherproof. The X300 Ultra is also versatile and can be attached to a pistol or a long gun since its Rail-Lock® system permits rapid attachment to and removal from either Universal or Picatinny rails. Its integral ambidextrous push/toggle switch provides one-finger operation for either momentary or constant-on operation. Optional DG grip switches are available for use with a pistol, and an XT07 tape switch permits the X300 Ultra to be activated when attached to a long gun without altering your grip on your weapon.
Technical Information
Bulb: LED
Light Output: 500 Lumens
Run Time: 1.5 hours
Battery: 2 CR123A
Material: Aluminum
Length: 3.60""
Weight: N/A
Conversion Kit includes everything for your basic conversion and to be 922r compliant for all Saiga 223, 7.62, 308, 5.45 Rifles and 410 & 20 Gauge Shotguns.
The Carolina Trigger Guard that comes with this kit has a grip nut built in.
This allows for an easy for conversion for the 410 shotguns and all rifles that do not have a grip nut hole in the receiver
The 308 rifle must have a new 3/16"" hole drilled for the mounting hardware.
Kit includes
1-Modified Tapco G2 FCG with Retaining Plate
1- Bolt on Carolina Billet Trigger Guard
6-Hole Plugs
1-Phoenix recoil reducing stock
1-Tapco SAW Grip in Black is standard with the kit, but can be upgraded to a different grip as an option."

The receiver was made in late November, 1943, and was re-barreled during an arsenal rebuild sometime in the summer of 1945. Perhaps it came ashore during the invasion of Europe in June of 1944, or was carried across Holland and into the forests of Belgium..

The rifle is as I obtained it from CMP, although I did highlight the windage sight markings. (Can be removed easily with bore cleaner).  The stock has a very faint EMcF cartouche which, although not the correct cartouche for this serial number, is a WWII era stock. It also exhibits a ""RA-P"" stamping (Raritan Arsenal rebuild proof) on the bottom of the stock grip - likely where the 1945 rebuild occurred. It has a D35382 6 curved side op rod, with relief cut. The barrel readings are a TE of 2+, and a ME of 1+, which are very good. I have shot two clips (16 rounds) through this rifle and it shoots extremely well.
Rifle comes in CMP hard case, with certificate, enbloc and armorer's hang tag.
Asking 1100.00 - OBRO. Additional photos and/or information can be provided upon request."

Item Description:
WMD brings the advanced performance of nickel boron to one of the most critical components on your LR-308.
WMD Guns exclusive Nickel Boron coating has a coefficient of friction of .07 and a Rockwell-C hardness of 70.

All components used are manufactured in the USA. Completely coated in their proprietary NiB-X coating and polished to a presentation-grade sheen, this top-quality BCG resists fouling, needs practically no lubrication, and can be cleaned with a quick wipe of a cloth. They have run thousands of rounds between cleanings without malfunctions.

Military personnel have praised its performance in desert conditions (where heavy lube buildup could attract deadly dust and grime). You’ll find that it provides extraordinary reliability, while dramatically reducing the time you spend cleaning.
Specifications:
**Bolt – Carpenter 158 heat-treated, shot peened and magnetic particle inspected. Manufactured to government drawings. Milspec gas rings. NiB-X coated (40% more wear-resistant than chrome).
**Extractor – Manufactured, heat treated, and hardened per government drawings. Black extractor buffer and heavy-duty spring. NiB-X coated.
**Firing Pin – Manufactured, heat-treated, hardened, chromed and certified per government drawings.
**Carrier – 8620 material, heat treated and case hardened. Manufacturing tolerances on inside diameters tightly controlled. NiB-X coated for durability and ease of cleaning.
**Gas Key – Hardened to USGI Specifications and attached using grade 8 hardened fasteners. NiB-X coated. Staked per military specifications.
**Cam pin – Manufactured, heat treated, hardened and certified per Government drawings. NiB-X Coated."
